Britain's Natalie Powell went out in the quarter-finals, later losing a repechage. Brazil's Mayar Aguiar and Slovenia's Anamari Velensek won bronze.
In the men's -100kg division, Lukas Krpalek of the Czech Republic beat Azerbaijani world number one Elmar Gasimov by ippon to win gold.
GB's Ben Fletcher lost in the last 32.
